external_knowledge:
- 'In the garden of nations' refers to the collection of countries;
- 'European countries' refers to countries in the geographic region of Europe;
- 'Life satisfaction score that blossoms above the global average' refers to life satisfaction scores greater than the average life satisfaction score of all countries.

sql:
SELECT c.country_name, q.life_satisfaction
FROM quality_of_life q
JOIN countries c ON q.country_id = c.country_id
WHERE q.life_satisfaction = (
  SELECT MAX(life_satisfaction) FROM quality_of_life
);

SELECT life_satisfaction, gdp_per_capita, employment_rate
FROM quality_of_life
ORDER BY life_satisfaction DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "High GDP per capita" is defined as a GDP per capita greater than 10,000 USD;
- "High life satisfaction" is defined as a life satisfaction score greater than 7;
- "Accessed by more than 10 users" means the total number of unique users who have viewed or downloaded the quality of life data is greater than 10.

sql:
SELECT life_expectancy
FROM quality_of_life
WHERE year = (SELECT MAX(year) FROM quality_of_life);

external_knowledge:
- 'Top-ranked countries in terms of life satisfaction' refers to countries ranked 1 to 3 within their regions based on average life satisfaction scores;
- 'Wealth is above average' means the average GDP per capita is greater than the average GDP per capita across all countries;
- 'Land stretches beyond the common horizon' means the region is in a country with an area greater than the average area of all countries.

- 'Average GDP per capita' is calculated using data from the World Bank for the year 2023;
- 'Views' refer to the number of times the quality of life data was accessed in 2023;
- 'Published reports' are reports that have been finalized and made available by users in the Research department.

- Life satisfaction score is a measure of happiness and well-being on a scale of 0 to 10;
- GDP per capita is a measure of a country's economic output per person, expressed in USD;
- "Exceptional contentment" refers to a life satisfaction score greater than 7.5;
- "Collective wealth of more than a million dollars per capita" means the sum of GDP per capita for countries in a region exceeds 1,000,000 USD.

- 'Beacons of social interest' refers to countries that have received a high number of views on social reports;
- 'Dawn of 2022' refers to the start of the year 2022;
- 'Life satisfaction score illuminates their path' refers to the average life satisfaction score of the country, which provides insight into the well-being of its citizens.

sql:
SELECT AVG(life_satisfaction) AS avg_life_satisfaction
FROM quality_of_life
WHERE quality_of_support_network > 80;
